# =============================================================================
# Review before pushing to a public repository
# =============================================================================
# 1. FONTS: api/fontlib/ contains flat .ttf/.woff2 files generated from
#    /System/Library/Fonts/Supplemental on macOS (Arial, Times New Roman,
#    Courier New, Georgia, Verdana, Tahoma, Trebuchet MS, Comic Sans, Impact).
#    These are Microsoft/Apple proprietary fonts and NOT redistributable.
#    They are excluded below. Cross-platform users should run
#    `api/scripts/build_fontlib.py` after cloning to regenerate from sources.
#
#    Vendored fonts (safe to commit):
#      - api/fontlib/vendor/liberation/  (SIL OFL 1.1, freely redistributable)
#      - api/fontlib/vendor/urw/         (AGPL3 + font-embedding exception;
#                                         see LICENSE; legal review recommended
#                                         before serving as WOFF2 commercially)
#
# 2. STORAGE: storage/ holds per-document uploads (user PDFs + extracted fonts
#    + saved revisions). 300MB+ of runtime data. Never commit.
#
# 3. PII: any PDFs at the repo root may contain personal data
#    (e.g., the receipt fixture). Excluded below.
#
# 4. CLAUDE: .claude/ holds local Claude Code config and may include personal
#    agent definitions. Excluded by default; remove the rule below if you
#    want to share agent configuration with collaborators.
# =============================================================================


# =============================================================================
